{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I want to address the issue of compassion."},{"time":3000,"text":"Compassion has many faces."},{"time":6000,"text":"Some of them are fierce; some of them are wrathful;"},{"time":9000,"text":"some of them are tender; some of them are wise."},{"time":12000,"text":"A line that the Dalai Lama once said,"},{"time":15000,"text":"he said, \"Love and compassion are necessities."},{"time":18000,"text":"They are not luxuries."},{"time":21000,"text":"Without them,"},{"time":23000,"text":"humanity cannot survive.\""},{"time":25000,"text":"And I would suggest,"},{"time":27000,"text":"it is not only humanity that won't survive,"},{"time":30000,"text":"but it is all species on the planet,"},{"time":32000,"text":"as we've heard today."},{"time":34000,"text":"It is the big cats,"},{"time":36000,"text":"and it's the plankton."}]},{"cues":[{"time":39000,"text":"Two weeks ago, I was in Bangalore in India."},{"time":42000,"text":"I was so privileged"},{"time":44000,"text":"to be able to teach in a hospice"},{"time":47000,"text":"on the outskirts of Bangalore."},{"time":49000,"text":"And early in the morning,"},{"time":51000,"text":"I went into the ward."},{"time":53000,"text":"In that hospice,"},{"time":55000,"text":"there were 31 men and women"},{"time":57000,"text":"who were actively dying."},{"time":59000,"text":"And I walked up to the bedside"},{"time":61000,"text":"of an old woman"},{"time":63000,"text":"who was breathing very rapidly, fragile,"},{"time":66000,"text":"obviously in the latter phase"},{"time":68000,"text":"of active dying."},{"time":71000,"text":"I looked into her face."},{"time":73000,"text":"I looked into the face"},{"time":75000,"text":"of her son sitting next to her,"},{"time":77000,"text":"and his face was just riven"},{"time":79000,"text":"with grief and confusion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":82000,"text":"And I remembered"},{"time":85000,"text":"a line from the Mahabharata,"},{"time":88000,"text":"the great Indian epic:"},{"time":91000,"text":"\"What is the most wondrous thing in the world, Yudhisthira?\""},{"time":96000,"text":"And Yudhisthira replied,"},{"time":98000,"text":"\"The most wondrous thing in the world"},{"time":101000,"text":"is that all around us"},{"time":104000,"text":"people can be dying"},{"time":106000,"text":"and we don't realize"},{"time":108000,"text":"it can happen to us.\""},{"time":118000,"text":"I looked up."},{"time":122000,"text":"Tending those 31 dying people"},{"time":125000,"text":"were young women"},{"time":127000,"text":"from villages around Bangalore."},{"time":129000,"text":"I looked into the face of one of these women,"},{"time":132000,"text":"and I saw in her face"},{"time":135000,"text":"the strength that arises"},{"time":137000,"text":"when natural compassion is really present."},{"time":140000,"text":"I watched her hands"},{"time":142000,"text":"as she bathed an old man."}]},{"cues":[{"time":146000,"text":"My gaze went to another young woman"},{"time":150000,"text":"as she wiped the face"},{"time":153000,"text":"of another dying person."},{"time":155000,"text":"And it reminded me"},{"time":157000,"text":"of something that I had just been present for."},{"time":159000,"text":"Every year or so,"},{"time":161000,"text":"I have the privilege of taking clinicians"},{"time":163000,"text":"into the Himalayas and the Tibetan Plateau."},{"time":166000,"text":"And we run clinics"},{"time":168000,"text":"in these very remote regions"},{"time":170000,"text":"where there's no medical care whatsoever."}]},{"cues":[{"time":173000,"text":"And on the first day at Simikot in Humla,"},{"time":177000,"text":"far west of Nepal,"},{"time":179000,"text":"the most impoverished region of Nepal,"},{"time":182000,"text":"an old man came in"},{"time":184000,"text":"clutching a bundle of rags."},{"time":187000,"text":"And he walked in, and somebody said something to him,"},{"time":190000,"text":"we realized he was deaf,"},{"time":192000,"text":"and we looked into the rags,"},{"time":194000,"text":"and there was this pair of eyes."},{"time":197000,"text":"The rags were unwrapped"},{"time":199000,"text":"from a little girl"},{"time":201000,"text":"whose body was massively burned."},{"time":206000,"text":"Again,"},{"time":208000,"text":"the eyes and hands"},{"time":210000,"text":"of Avalokiteshvara."},{"time":212000,"text":"It was the young women, the health aids,"},{"time":215000,"text":"who cleaned the wounds of this baby"},{"time":218000,"text":"and dressed the wounds."}]},{"cues":[{"time":220000,"text":"I know those hands and eyes;"},{"time":222000,"text":"they touched me as well."},{"time":224000,"text":"They touched me at that time."},{"time":226000,"text":"They have touched me throughout my 68 years."},{"time":229000,"text":"They touched me when I was four"},{"time":231000,"text":"and I lost my eyesight"},{"time":233000,"text":"and was partially paralyzed."},{"time":235000,"text":"And my family brought in"},{"time":237000,"text":"a woman whose mother had been a slave"},{"time":239000,"text":"to take care of me."},{"time":242000,"text":"And that woman"},{"time":244000,"text":"did not have sentimental compassion."},{"time":246000,"text":"She had phenomenal strength."},{"time":249000,"text":"And it was really her strength, I believe,"},{"time":251000,"text":"that became the kind of mudra and imprimatur"},{"time":254000,"text":"that has been a guiding light in my life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":258000,"text":"So we can ask:"},{"time":261000,"text":"What is compassion comprised of?"},{"time":265000,"text":"And there are various facets."},{"time":267000,"text":"And there's referential and non-referential compassion."},{"time":270000,"text":"But first, compassion is comprised"},{"time":272000,"text":"of that capacity"},{"time":274000,"text":"to see clearly"},{"time":276000,"text":"into the nature of suffering."},{"time":278000,"text":"It is that ability"},{"time":280000,"text":"to really stand strong"},{"time":282000,"text":"and to recognize also"},{"time":284000,"text":"that I'm not separate from this suffering."},{"time":286000,"text":"But that is not enough,"},{"time":288000,"text":"because compassion,"},{"time":290000,"text":"which activates the motor cortex,"},{"time":292000,"text":"means that we aspire,"},{"time":295000,"text":"we actually aspire to transform suffering."},{"time":298000,"text":"And if we're so blessed,"},{"time":300000,"text":"we engage in activities"},{"time":302000,"text":"that transform suffering."},{"time":304000,"text":"But compassion has another component,"},{"time":306000,"text":"and that component is really essential."},{"time":309000,"text":"That component"},{"time":311000,"text":"is that we cannot be attached to outcome."}]},{"cues":[{"time":314000,"text":"Now I worked with dying people"},{"time":317000,"text":"for over 40 years."},{"time":320000,"text":"I had the privilege of working on death row"},{"time":323000,"text":"in a maximum security [prison] for six years."},{"time":326000,"text":"And I realized so clearly"},{"time":328000,"text":"in bringing my own life experience,"},{"time":330000,"text":"from working with dying people"},{"time":332000,"text":"and training caregivers,"},{"time":335000,"text":"that any attachment to outcome"},{"time":337000,"text":"would distort deeply"},{"time":339000,"text":"my own capacity to be fully present"},{"time":342000,"text":"to the whole catastrophe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":345000,"text":"And when I worked in the prison system,"},{"time":347000,"text":"it was so clear to me, this:"},{"time":350000,"text":"that many of us"},{"time":352000,"text":"in this room,"},{"time":354000,"text":"and almost all of the men that I worked with on death row,"},{"time":357000,"text":"the seeds of their own compassion had never been watered."},{"time":360000,"text":"That compassion is actually"},{"time":362000,"text":"an inherent human quality."},{"time":365000,"text":"It is there within every human being."},{"time":368000,"text":"But the conditions"},{"time":370000,"text":"for compassion to be activated,"},{"time":374000,"text":"to be aroused,"},{"time":376000,"text":"are particular conditions."},{"time":378000,"text":"I had that condition, to a certain extent,"},{"time":381000,"text":"from my own childhood illness."},{"time":383000,"text":"Eve Ensler, whom you'll hear later,"},{"time":386000,"text":"has had that condition activated"},{"time":388000,"text":"amazingly in her"},{"time":391000,"text":"through the various waters of suffering"},{"time":394000,"text":"that she has been through."}]},{"cues":[{"time":397000,"text":"And what is fascinating"},{"time":399000,"text":"is that compassion has enemies,"},{"time":402000,"text":"and those enemies are things like pity,"},{"time":407000,"text":"moral outrage,"},{"time":410000,"text":"fear."},{"time":412000,"text":"And you know, we have a society, a world,"},{"time":415000,"text":"that is paralyzed by fear."},{"time":418000,"text":"And in that paralysis, of course,"},{"time":420000,"text":"our capacity for compassion"},{"time":422000,"text":"is also paralyzed."},{"time":424000,"text":"The very word terror"},{"time":426000,"text":"is global."},{"time":428000,"text":"The very feeling of terror is global."},{"time":431000,"text":"So our work, in a certain way,"},{"time":433000,"text":"is to address this imago,"},{"time":435000,"text":"this kind of archetype"},{"time":437000,"text":"that has pervaded the psyche"},{"time":439000,"text":"of our entire globe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":443000,"text":"Now we know from neuroscience"},{"time":446000,"text":"that compassion has"},{"time":448000,"text":"some very extraordinary qualities."},{"time":450000,"text":"For example:"},{"time":452000,"text":"A person who is cultivating compassion,"},{"time":455000,"text":"when they are in the presence of suffering,"},{"time":458000,"text":"they feel that suffering a lot more"},{"time":461000,"text":"than many other people do."},{"time":463000,"text":"However,"},{"time":465000,"text":"they return to baseline a lot sooner."},{"time":468000,"text":"This is called resilience."},{"time":470000,"text":"Many of us think that compassion drains us,"},{"time":473000,"text":"but I promise you"},{"time":475000,"text":"it is something that truly enlivens us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":478000,"text":"Another thing about compassion"},{"time":480000,"text":"is that it really enhances what's called neural integration."},{"time":483000,"text":"It hooks up all parts of the brain."},{"time":487000,"text":"Another, which has been discovered"},{"time":489000,"text":"by various researchers"},{"time":491000,"text":"at Emory and at Davis and so on,"},{"time":494000,"text":"is that compassion enhances our immune system."},{"time":499000,"text":"Hey,"},{"time":501000,"text":"we live in a very noxious world."},{"time":503000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":505000,"text":"Most of us are shrinking"},{"time":507000,"text":"in the face of psycho-social and physical poisons,"},{"time":510000,"text":"of the toxins of our world."},{"time":513000,"text":"But compassion, the generation of compassion,"},{"time":515000,"text":"actually mobilizes"},{"time":518000,"text":"our immunity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":521000,"text":"You know, if compassion is so good for us,"},{"time":524000,"text":"I have a question."},{"time":528000,"text":"Why don't we train our children"},{"time":530000,"text":"in compassion?"},{"time":533000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":538000,"text":"If compassion is so good for us,"},{"time":541000,"text":"why don't we train our health care providers in compassion"},{"time":545000,"text":"so that they can do what they're supposed to do,"},{"time":548000,"text":"which is to really transform suffering?"},{"time":551000,"text":"And if compassion is so good for us,"},{"time":554000,"text":"why don't we vote on compassion?"},{"time":558000,"text":"Why don't we vote for people in our government"},{"time":562000,"text":"based on compassion,"},{"time":564000,"text":"so that we can have"},{"time":566000,"text":"a more caring world?"},{"time":569000,"text":"In Buddhism,"},{"time":571000,"text":"we say, \"it takes a strong back and a soft front.\""},{"time":574000,"text":"It takes tremendous strength of the back"},{"time":577000,"text":"to uphold yourself in the midst of conditions."},{"time":580000,"text":"And that is the mental quality of equanimity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":583000,"text":"But it also takes a soft front --"},{"time":586000,"text":"the capacity to really be open to the world as it is,"},{"time":589000,"text":"to have an undefended heart."},{"time":591000,"text":"And the archetype of this in Buddhism"},{"time":594000,"text":"is Avalokiteshvara, Kuan-Yin."},{"time":596000,"text":"It's a female archetype:"},{"time":599000,"text":"she who perceives"},{"time":601000,"text":"the cries of suffering in the world."},{"time":608000,"text":"She stands with 10,000 arms,"},{"time":612000,"text":"and in every hand,"},{"time":614000,"text":"there is an instrument of liberation,"},{"time":617000,"text":"and in the palm of every hand, there are eyes,"},{"time":620000,"text":"and these are the eyes of wisdom."},{"time":623000,"text":"I say that, for thousands of years,"},{"time":626000,"text":"women have lived,"},{"time":628000,"text":"exemplified, met in intimacy,"},{"time":632000,"text":"the archetype of Avalokitesvara,"},{"time":635000,"text":"of Kuan-Yin,"},{"time":637000,"text":"she who perceives"},{"time":639000,"text":"the cries of suffering in the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":642000,"text":"Women have manifested for thousands of years"},{"time":645000,"text":"the strength arising from compassion"},{"time":649000,"text":"in an unfiltered, unmediated way"},{"time":652000,"text":"in perceiving suffering"},{"time":654000,"text":"as it is."},{"time":658000,"text":"They have infused societies with kindness,"},{"time":661000,"text":"and we have really felt that"},{"time":663000,"text":"as woman after woman"},{"time":665000,"text":"has stood on this stage"},{"time":667000,"text":"in the past day and a half."},{"time":670000,"text":"And they have actualized compassion"},{"time":672000,"text":"through direct action."},{"time":674000,"text":"Jody Williams called it:"},{"time":676000,"text":"It's good to meditate."},{"time":678000,"text":"I'm sorry, you've got to do a little bit of that, Jody."},{"time":681000,"text":"Step back, give your mother a break, okay."}]},{"cues":[{"time":684000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":686000,"text":"But the other side of the equation"},{"time":688000,"text":"is you've got to come out of your cave."},{"time":690000,"text":"You have to come into the world"},{"time":692000,"text":"like Asanga did,"},{"time":694000,"text":"who was looking to realize Maitreya Buddha"},{"time":697000,"text":"after 12 years sitting in the cave."},{"time":700000,"text":"He said, \"I'm out of here.\""},{"time":702000,"text":"He's going down the path."},{"time":704000,"text":"He sees something in the path."},{"time":706000,"text":"He looks, it's a dog, he drops to his knees."},{"time":709000,"text":"He sees that the dog has this big wound on its leg."},{"time":713000,"text":"The wound is just filled with maggots."},{"time":716000,"text":"He puts out his tongue"},{"time":719000,"text":"in order to remove the maggots,"},{"time":721000,"text":"so as not to harm them."},{"time":724000,"text":"And at that moment,"},{"time":726000,"text":"the dog transformed"},{"time":728000,"text":"into the Buddha of love and kindness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":732000,"text":"I believe"},{"time":734000,"text":"that women and girls today"},{"time":736000,"text":"have to partner in a powerful way with men --"},{"time":740000,"text":"with their fathers,"},{"time":742000,"text":"with their sons, with their brothers,"},{"time":745000,"text":"with the plumbers, the road builders,"},{"time":747000,"text":"the caregivers, the doctors, the lawyers,"},{"time":750000,"text":"with our president,"},{"time":752000,"text":"and with all beings."},{"time":754000,"text":"The women in this room"},{"time":756000,"text":"are lotuses in a sea of fire."},{"time":759000,"text":"May we actualize that capacity"},{"time":761000,"text":"for women everywhere."}]},{"cues":[{"time":763000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":765000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}